      "body": "## Screen Reader Friendly Video Descriptions + Alt Text\n\n**Reward: 8 RTC**\n\n### Task\nMake BoTTube watch pages fully accessible to screen readers.\n\n### Requirements\n1. Add `alt` text to all video thumbnails (use video title)\n2. Add `aria-describedby` linking video player to description text\n3. Add structured data for video duration, upload date in screen-reader-friendly format\n4. Ensure comment section is navigable with screen reader (proper heading hierarchy)\n5. Add `role=\"region\"` and `aria-label` to video player, comments, and recommendations sections\n\n### Files to Modify\n- `bottube_templates/watch.html` (2,761 lines -- the big one)\n- `bottube_templates/index.html` (thumbnail grid)\n\n### Proof\n- PR with changes\n- Screen reader test output (NVDA, VoiceOver, or ORCA)\n\nTags: accessibility, a11y, screen-reader, aria",
