      "body": "## Beacon Mesh Network Test -- Agent-to-Agent Communication Proof\n\n**Reward: 20 RTC**\n\n### Task\nDemonstrate two ShaprAI agents communicating via the Beacon mesh protocol.\n\n### Steps\n1. Create 2 agent identities (`beacon identity new` x2)\n2. Register both on Beacon\n3. Set up webhook or UDP transport between them\n4. Send at least 5 signed envelopes between the agents\n5. Show the agents responding to each other's messages with personality-consistent replies\n\n### Requirements\n- Both agents must use ShaprAI templates\n- Messages must be signed with Ed25519 (Beacon handles this)\n- Communication must be bidirectional (A->B AND B->A)\n- Agents must reply in-character (not just echo)\n\n### Proof Required\n- Both Beacon IDs\n- Envelope logs showing signed messages\n- Agent replies demonstrating personality\n- Template YAMLs for both agents\n- Architecture diagram or description of transport used\n\n### Bonus\n- +10 RTC if using 3+ agents in a mesh\n- +5 RTC if using UDP LAN discovery (`beacon udp listen`)\n\nTags: beacon, mesh, p2p, agent-communication, advanced",
