      "body": "## Accessibility Audit and Fixes for Elyan Labs UIs\n\n**Reward: 10 RTC**\n\n### Why This Matters\nThe Flameholder (project lead) has TBI and mobility challenges. Accessibility is not a checkbox -- it is core to our mission.\n\n### Task\nRun a WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility audit on any Elyan Labs web UI and submit fixes:\n\n**Eligible UIs:**\n- BoTTube (bottube.ai)\n- RustChain Block Explorer (rustchain.org/explorer)\n- Beacon Atlas (rustchain.org/beacon)\n- ShaprAI docs (if web UI exists)\n\n### Minimum Requirements\n- Test with keyboard-only navigation\n- Check color contrast ratios (4.5:1 minimum for normal text)\n- Verify ARIA labels on interactive elements\n- Check focus indicators\n- Test with a screen reader (NVDA, VoiceOver, or ORCA)\n\n### Deliverables\n- Audit report (issue or markdown) with WCAG references\n- PR with fixes for at least 3 issues found\n- Before/after screenshots or screen reader output\n\n### Bonus\n- +5 RTC for fixing 5+ issues\n- +3 RTC for screen reader testing proof (video or transcript)\n\nTags: accessibility, wcag, a11y, ui, good-first-issue",
